# Web Development Rules

- **CONSOLIDATE CSS** - Avoid duplication, create reusable classes
- **DON'T DUPLICATE JS OR CSS** - Search for code before adding
- **NAME BY PURPOSE NOT LOCATION** - CSS classes should describe what they are, not where
- **ORGANIZE BY ELEMENT TYPE** - Group CSS by element, not by page/section  
- **USE CSS CUSTOM PROPERTIES** - Variables instead of hardcoded values
- **NO INLINE STYLES** - Keep all styling in CSS files
- **BREAK INTO PARTIALS** - Create reusable Eleventy partials, search before creating
- **CHECK OUTPUT** - Verify generated HTML matches expectations
- **MEANINGFUL PAGE TITLES** - Unique, descriptive titles for SEO
- **VALID HTML** - Validate markup and fix errors
